text:
Lincoln County is a county in the U.S. state of Wyoming. As of the 2010 census, 18,106 people lived there. Its county seat is Kemmerer.
Its western border abuts the east border of the state of Utah.
History.
Lincoln County was created on February 21, 1911. The county was named for Abraham Lincoln, 16th President of the United States.
